SIMPLE: supervise
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supervise
<hw>Su`per*vise"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Supervised</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Supervising</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>super-</ets> + L. <ets>visere</ets> to look at attentively, to
view, surely, intens. from <ets>videre</ets>, <ets>visum</ets>, to see.
Cf. <er>Survise</er>, and <er>Survey</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
oversee for direction; to superintend; to inspect with authority;
<as>as, to <ex>supervise</ex> the construction of a steam engine, or the
printing of a book</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To look over so as to read; to peruse.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Superintend</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supervise</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Supervise
<hw>Su`per*vise"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Supervision; inspection.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supervision</ent>⟦br⟧
